The paper discusses the performance analysis of ultra-dense networks (UDNs) in wireless communication, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also incorporates multi-slope path loss and general fading distributions, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the fundamental limits of wireless network densification, which can be related to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
